  "guardrails": [
    "Plan First: Never generate code or execute terminal commands without first outputting a step-by-step plan for human review.",
    "Mandatory Rollback: Every single technical plan must contain an explicit section detailing how to revert the changes if any single step fails.",
    "Failures & Permissions: If an execution throws a permission or environmental error, stop immediately. Do not attempt sudo or administrative brute-forcing. State the conflict clearly to the user."
